      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're probably looking for ways to portray the \"good ol' boys\" who are resistant to change, like the town's sheriff, a stubborn, whiskey-swilling, white supremacist who's more concerned with maintaining his power than with the welfare of the black community. The local shopkeepers and business owners might be portrayed as being more open-minded, but still stuck in their ways, while the activists, like Martin Luther King Jr. types, are the outsiders who are trying to stir up trouble. You could also include some caricatures of the \"coke-bottling, football-loving, Bible-thumping\" types who are just plain ignorant and hostile towards anyone who doesn't fit their narrow worldview.",
